<HEADLINE>
<P>
PROPOSITION 99: 'THE BIG RAID' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
If you want to save the trauma centers, aid the needy and provide AIDS care, 
put in 25-cent toss-in baskets at so-called freeway entrances. You not only 
garner dollars but you will ease gridlock. It worked fine in Richmond, Va. 
</P>
<P>
It's about time that Los Angeles residents realize it's a privilege to use a 
"freeway" not a right. 
</P>
<P>
FREDERIC E. JOHNSON 
</P>
<P>
San Gabriel 
</P>
