<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHERYL DANIELS LEADS BOWLING TOURNAMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cheryl Daniels averaged 224 to take a 15-pin lead over Cindy Coburn after 
Sunday's first round of the $35,000 Ladies Pro Bowlers Tour Lady LaMode Open at 
Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
Daniels, a nine-year tour veteran who has never won a title, finished the 
opening round with a nine-game total of 2,016 pins. Daniels has finished second 
three times in her career. 
</P>
<P>
Coburn, trying for her 13th career title, had 2,001 pins. 
</P>
<P>
Robin Romeo, winner of the Canoga Park tournament last Wednesday, was third at 
1,999. 
</P>
<P>
Paula Drake was fourth at 1,966, followed by Jan Barnowsky with 1,951 and Anne 
Marie Pike with 1,925. 
</P>
<P>
The tournament ends Wednesday night when the top six bowlers will advance to 
the finals. First prize is $7,000. 
</P>
