The Soviet Union carried out an underground nuclear test near Semipalatinsk in 
Central Asia aimed at "modernizing military hardware," Tass reported Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The official news agency said the blast early Sunday yielded between 20 and 150 
kilotons. No abnormal radiation was detected, Tass said. 
</P>
