<P>
The Federal Deposit Insurance Corp. has charged former White House budget 
director Bert Lance and a Calhoun company with defaulting on loan payments to a 
now-defunct Tennessee bank. The U.S. District Court suit seeks $1.5 million 
from Lance and the Kris Co. It alleges that Lance and the company defaulted on 
payments to the United American Bank of Knoxville for four separate loans and 
renewal agreements dating to late 1981. The suit, filed in Rome, Ga., was made 
public Thursday after U.S. District Judge Harold L. Murphy denied a request by 
the government's lawyers to keep it secret for 20 days. Lance said he had not 
seen a copy of the suit. Lance declined to talk about the Kris Co, saying it 
was a "personal company." 
