<TEXT>
<P>
Lumber production, orders and shipments decreased as the record-breaking cold 
wave engulfed 12 Western states last week, a trade association reported. The 
Western Wood Products Assn. reported lumber production of 307 million board 
feet, down 76 million feet from the previous week. The association reported 
orders for 342 million board feet, down 37 million feet from the previous week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
