<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
FOUNTAIN VALLEY; 
</P>
<P>
SCHOLARSHIP ENDOWMENT CREATED BY CHAMBER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Fountain Valley Chamber of Commerce has established a $5,000 scholarship 
endowment to help individuals who live or work in the community to advance 
their education. 
</P>
<P>
The endowment, to Coastline Community College, will be used to help qualified 
students and business professionals continue academic or vocational education 
and training, said Joel Vest, executive vice president of the chamber. 
</P>
<P>
Additional information about chamber scholarships can be obtained by contacting 
Thomas Snyder, executive director of the Coastline Community College 
Foundation, at 241-6243. 
</P>
</TEXT>
