<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA DEFEATS IRVINE IN VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
California lost the first game, then rallied to defeat UC Irvine in five games 
Sunday in a nonconference men's volleyball match at Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
The Bears won, 6-15, 15-5, 15-9, 12-15, 15-7. 
</P>
<P>
Andrew Katsman had 24 kills and Justin Cox had 19 for the Bears (7-1). David 
Pettker had 25 kills and Steve Florentine 21 for Irvine (3-10). 
</P>
