<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION; 
</P>
<P>
GEORGIA GOVERNOR'S AUNT STRANGLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CARTERSVILLE, Ga. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An aunt of Gov. Joe Frank Harris, found slain in her home over the weekend, was 
strangled, perhaps by a robber, police said today. 
</P>
<P>
Allie Morrow Roper, 75, a sister of Harris' mother, Frances Morrow Harris, was 
found dead Sunday morning after she failed to pick up neighbors for church. The 
woman, who lived alone, apparently was killed Saturday night, police said. She 
was found unclothed and bound. The Harris family was "in shock" over the 
slaying, said Barbara Morgan, spokeswoman for the governor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
