<P>
SAN DIEGO FWY TO CLOSE OVERNIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
All northbound lanes of the San Diego Freeway between the Santa Ana and Corona 
del Mar freeways will be closed at 9 p.m. tonight for construction work, 
Caltrans officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The closure is needed so crews can install so-called K-rails, the concrete 
barriers that separate traffic from construction work, officials said. The 
northbound lanes are scheduled to reopen at 5 a.m. Tuesday. The Santa Ana 
Freeway will remain open. 
</P>
<P>
The closure on the San Diego Freeway is part of a widening project that 
includes installation of car-pool lanes. A five-mile segment of the northbound 
car-pool lane is already open from the Springdale Street bridge in Westminster 
to the San Gabriel River Freeway in Seal Beach. The entire project is scheduled 
for completion in July, 1990. 
</P>
</TEXT>
