<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND; 
</P>
<P>
HUNTINGTON BEACH MAN FLEES POLICE; 150-MILE CHASE ENDS IN THE OCEAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Huntington Beach man led authorities on 150-mile chase over 10 freeways in 
Los Angeles and Orange counties early this morning before driving his red 
Camaro into the ocean off the Huntington Beach pier. 
</P>
<P>
An Orange County Sheriff's Department boat plucked James Hamilton, 23, from the 
chilly water about 5:20 a.m., as he clung to a pier support, CHP Lt. Jerry 
Jewett said. Hamilton was taken to a hospital for treatment of hypothermia and 
scrapes on his stomach. He was arrested on suspicion of evading police and 
damaging city property. 
</P>
<P>
Brea police officers began pursuing Hamilton about 2:45 a.m. on the southbound 
Orange Freeway because they believed that his car was involved with a murder 
investigation, Jewett said. Brea police lost sight of Hamilton, and CHP 
officers continued the pursuit at speeds of up to 105 m.p.h. 
</P>
</TEXT>
