<HEADLINE>
<P>
SARA LEE TO BUY CHAMPION FIRM FOR $320.9 MILLION; 
</P>
<P>
CHAMPION CLOTHING FIRM OKS BUYOUT BY SARA LEE SUBSIDIARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PITTSFORD, N.Y. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Champion Products Inc., a maker of athletic and leisure clothing, has agreed to 
be sold to Sara Lee Corp. of Chicago in a deal valued at $320.9 million, 
Champion officials announced today. 
</P>
<P>
Champion, which saw profits rise 114% last year to $14.8 million, has been 
trying to fight off a hostile takeover attempt by a New York investment group. 
</P>
<P>
The agreement between Champion and Sara Lee, a $10-billion food and consumer 
products company, calls for a wholly owned subsidiary of Sara Lee to begin 
offering $77 a share for Champion stock this week. 
</P>
<P>
The company said there are 4,167,700 outstanding shares of fully diluted stock, 
including various convertible stock options. 
</P>
<P>
Champion stock on Friday closed at 63 5/8, a record high, on the American Stock 
Exchange. 
</P>
<P>
Phonicam Corp., the New York firm that has been trying to buy Champion since 
1986, has been accumulating the company's stock and offered to buy Champion in 
December at $55 a share. It upped the offer in January to $61. 
</P>
</TEXT>
